CatDescriptText: Cutline of image published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper December 28, 1946, pg. 11, reads: "Steelmen Attend Parley - Playing important roles during the recent historic United Steelworkers (CIO) parleys in Pittsburgh's Keystone Hotel were the high ranking union officials. Left to right: Carl Dickerson, committeeman of Duquesne USW, Local 1256; Alec McJennett, president, USW-CIO Local 1414, Gardens, Calif.; Boyd Wilson, international representative, USW-CIO of Pittsburgh and St. Louis; James G. Thimmes, international vice president, United Steelworker, Lucius Love, president, United Steelworkers, Local 1433 of the Inland Steel Company, Chicago, Ill.  - Harris Photon"
TitMainTitle: Union officials Carl Dickerson, Alec McJennett, Boyd Wilson, James G. Thimmes, and Lucius Love at United Steelworkers, USW-CIO event in Keystone Hotel
